<subSubSection id="C31343D2FFCAFFAF6180F880C1D3F858" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB61059FFCAFFAF6180F880C1D3F858" blockId="6.[151,1436,1770,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCAFFAF6180F880C46FF8F5" bold="true" box="[199,308,1878,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Remarks</emphasis>
. Present species is characterised by presence of single posterior areola (which consists a depression on anterior side) on AD, denticulous process on tibiae I and II psteroventrally, ovipositor long. This species has some similarity with ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFCAFFAF60C8F848C7E2F83D" baseAuthorityName="Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[399,697,1950,1976]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellosus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCAFFAF60C8F848C7E2F83D" box="[399,697,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Copidognathus lamellosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group’ but differ from that group by the presence of single posterior areola on AD in contrast to two circular posterior areolae present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFCAFFAF6286F814C162F859" baseAuthorityName="Lohmann" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[961,1081,1986,2012]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellosus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFCAFFAF6286F814C162F859" box="[961,1081,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">lamellosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
